{"type":"user.message","data":{"content":"I'm starting a new .NET MAUI project on .NET 10. I found a tutorial that says\nto add `ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"True\"` to my ContentPage to handle the iPhone\nnotch. Is this the right approach? Also, the tutorial mentions using\n`IgnoreSafeArea=\"True\"` on a Grid for a background image. Are these correct\nfor .NET 10?\n","transformedContent":"<current_datetime>2026-04-29T01:09:43.950Z</current_datetime>\n\nI'm starting a new .NET MAUI project on .NET 10. I found a tutorial that says\nto add `ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"True\"` to my ContentPage to handle the iPhone\nnotch. Is this the right approach? Also, the tutorial mentions using\n`IgnoreSafeArea=\"True\"` on a Grid for a background image. Are these correct\nfor .NET 10?","attachments":[],"interactionId":"95448652-e9ed-433f-8856-56a7ada34241"},"id":"ddef2a12-a424-4c93-9904-2715533f0f89","timestamp":"2026-04-29T01:09:43.950Z","parentId":"9400421e-e60f-4e3b-95eb-6c9c435eaa03"}
